docs/sandbox/guide.md:73:Start with `UnixLocalSandboxClient` for local development on macOS or Linux. On Windows, use `DockerSandboxClient` or a hosted provider instead. On any supported platform, move to `DockerSandboxClient` when you need container isolation or image parity, or to a hosted provider when you need provider-managed execution.
docs/sandbox/guide.md:75:In most cases, the `SandboxAgent` definition stays the same while the sandbox client and its options change in [`SandboxRunConfig`][agents.run_config.SandboxRunConfig]. See [Sandbox clients](clients.md) for local, Docker, hosted, and remote-mount options.
docs/sandbox/guide.md:217:Manifest entry paths are workspace-relative. They cannot be absolute paths or escape the workspace with `..`, which keeps the workspace contract portable across local, Docker, and hosted clients.
